  m_text: "The rudder is a type of so-called oar rudder, which came into use in the
    14th and 15th centuries. The rudder, made of oak, is made of several parts. The
    parts are connected to each other with iron plates.\n\nOnly their impressions
    remain on the surface of the wood. On the other side, you can see the pins with
    which the rudder was hung in place on the ship\u2019s stern frame. "
